<div style="color:#990000; font-size:14px" align="center"><strong>Instructions for Course Reserves Request</strong></div>

<p><strong>The course reserves request form is for Shady Grove faculty only</strong>. USG faculty affiliated with BS, SU, TU, UB, UMB, UMBC, UMCP, UMES, &amp; UMUC can submit book request for course reserves materials at the Shady Grove Library.  Please be aware that processing reserve requests take time. Submit your request as early as possible to ensure that material needed for course reserves is available to the students on time. It is quite likely that material requested may not be in the libraryâ€™s collection and library may need to order the material.  New materials are first cataloged then they are processed for courser reserves.  Sometimes materials requested is already on loan to patron, which requires recalling and causes further delay in processing the reserves requests.   We make all attempts to process course reserves requests promptly, but there is a heavy demand in the beginning of the semester, your request will be processed in the order in which it is received.  You are encouraged to provide a copy of the syllabi to the library.</p>
<br />
